<center><font size=7><b>Dizzy 1</b></font></center>
<center>Number of entries found: 7</center><p>
<center>
<table width=600>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Tips</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>Flaming Torch:
Find this in the first screen, to the right. Drop it next to the cauldron at the
start.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Grease Gun:
In the first screen, to the left. Drop it on top of the mining cart.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Crow Bar:
In the cliffs. Drop it on top of the trap door at the bottom of the cliffs.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Purse of Gold:
Go into the screen on the right from the haunted chimney then go into the cave.
Get the purse and drop it on top of the bucket near the hermit's house.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ghost Hunters Laser Gun:
Pick it up and fall into the ghost at the haunted chimney.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Miner's Hard Hat:
Destroys rocks that falls on you in different places.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Broken Heart:
In the castle. Drop it on top of the statue where the broken-hearted woman
stands.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Three-In-One:
In the room two screens from the purse of gold. Drop it next to the drawbridge.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Plastic Raincoat:
Protects you from the raindrops that fall from the clouds.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Spell, The Ingredients:
<pre>
Clouds of Silver Lining    Jump on top of hermit's house.
Vampire Dux Feather        Just outside the castle.
Troll Brew                 Just inside the castle.
Leprechaun's Wig           In mine shaft, just near the bolt cutters.
</pre>
Put all the ingredients in the cauldron, drop the bottle in then get the potion.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Go in the castle and drop the bottle next to Zaks, and that's it - you've won.
 <i>(YS Smash Tips)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Multiface pokes</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD><table border="0">
<tr>
<td WIDTH="200" ALIGN="LEFT"><B><U>DESCRIPTION</B></U></TD>
<td WIDTH="200" ALIGN="LEFT"><B><U>POKE(s)</B></U></TD>
</TR>
<tr><td>Lives = x</td><td>62789,x (x = 1-255)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Walk Speed = x</td><td>62789,x (x = 1-7)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Infinite Lives</td><td>62745,0</td></tr>
<tr><td>Immunity</td><td>54216,0</td></tr>
<tr><td>Walk through walls</td><td>60137,201</td></tr>
</table>
<BR><BR><B>Change x to whatever value you wish, using the POKE&nbsp;option on the ZXAM GUI</B>
<BR>With the "Walk Speed" POKE, the default setting is 4 , 1= Fast, 7= Slow.
<BR>I would advise <U>NOT</U> using the Immunity POKE as there are some parts of the game
that you can sink through and end up in "limbo" and have to abort the game :(<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <i>(Gerard Sweeney in Hack Attack III)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Type-in hacks</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>This can be found in <a href="ftp://ftp.void.jump.org/pub/sinclair/magazines/YourSinclair/Issue40/Tape/">this issue of Pokes</a> in the alphabetical section.
 <i>(Cover Tape in Your Sinclair issue 40)</i> 

<br><hr>
This can be found in <a href="ftp://ftp.void.jump.org/pub/sinclair/magazines/YourSinclair/Issue64/Tape/">this issue of Pokerama</a>.
 <i>(Cover Tape in Your Sinclair issue 64)</i> 

<br><hr>
This can be found in <a href="ftp://ftp.void.jump.org/pub/sinclair/magazines/YourSinclair/Issue75/Tape/">this issue of Pokerama</a>.
 <i>(Cover Tape in Your Sinclair issue 75)</i> 

<br><hr>
This can be found in <a href="ftp://ftp.void.jump.org/pub/sinclair/magazines/YourSinclair/Issue84/Tape/">this issue of Hack Attack</a>.
 <i>(Cover Tape in Your Sinclair issue 84)</i> 

<br><hr>
<pre>
 10 LET imm=0: LET liv=0
 20 INPUT "Immortal? "; LINE a$
 30 IF a$="y" THEN LET imm=221
 40 INPUT "lives? "; LINE a$
 50 IF a$="y" THEN LET liv=245
 60 LOAD ""CODE
 70 FOR f=23352 TO 23361
 80 READ a: POKE f,a: NEXT f
 90 RANDOMIZE USR 23296
100 DATA 175,50,200,imm,50
110 DATA 26,1iv,195,182,92
</pre>
 <i>(YS Smash Tips)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
</table></center><P>
